# Database Rules

- PostgreSQL as primary store; Redis only for queues/cache
- All schema changes via **Prisma migrations** (never manual prod edits)
- Use **UUID** primary keys
- Add indexes for query paths (status, externalId, createdAt, unique constraints)
- No business logic in SQL / raw queries unless justified and reviewed
- Soft-delete or status enums where auditability matters
- Map domain enums explicitly in Prisma
- Keep migrations small and reversible where possible
